def insert_after_character(string):
    return string.replace('o', 'oa')

# Example usage of the function
print(insert_after_character('Hello World'))  # "Helloa World"
print(insert_after_character('foobar'))  # "foobaar"
print(insert_after_character('spam and eggs'))  # "spam and eags"
